{
  "texts": [
    "Experiment SetupWe use two algorithms, GA and RL, to find WCET.",
    "We compare their results with a random algorithm as the baseline to find out if they are worth to be used for finding WCET or not.",
    "In addition, a comparison is made between our GA and RL to see which algorithm does a better job in finding WCET.The experiment has been done on a system with 12 Intel Core Processor (Haswell, no TSX, IBRS) cores, 64 GB RAM, with Ubuntu 22.04 as OS.",
    "It was patched with PREEMPT RT patch [105].",
    "The PREEMPT RT patch makes the Linux kernel more suitable for real-time applications by allowing tasks to be preempted anywhere, except in critical sections protected by spinlocks."
  ]
}